# PRISM Operator Hub Hardening Walkthrough

This walkthrough details the design, implementation, and successful verification of the **Live Console WebSocket Engine**, **MCP Server Monitoring System**, and **SQLite-persisted Micro Support Desk** in PRISM's operator hub. All components are implemented with zero mocks, stubs, or simulations, providing full real-time telemetry and database integrity.

---

## 1. Accomplished Features & Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    UI[HTML Frontend logs-tab] -->|REST /api/support/tickets| DS[Dashboard Service API]
    UI -->|WebSocket Subscription| WS[WebSocket Live Console Engine]
    DS -->|Transactions| CSS[Chat Session Store SQLite]
    CSS -->|SQLite DB| DB[(prism-activity.db)]
```

### A. Live Console WebSocket & REST Hydration
- Purged parser-locking `<script>` tags from `tab-logs.html` to guarantee dynamic tab loading capability.
- Implemented robust socket candidate auto-detection (`dashboardWs`, `__prismWs`, or `ws`) in `tab-logs.js` to hook into active real-time console frames.
- Configured a fallback authed WebSocket initialization (`/ws?token=...`) if no active candidate is found.
- Added `/api/debug/console?limit=500` REST fallback hydration during `initLogsTab()` to instantly pull previous execution traces on load.
- Added console filters (Stdout, Stderr, MCP logs), log cap management, pause/resume state persistence, and copy-to-clipboard functionality.

### B. Live MCP Servers Diagnostic Hub
- Built active server status polling inside `initLogsTab()`, querying `/api/mcp/servers` every 5 seconds.
- Created premium UI status indicators mapping server statuses (`connected`, `retrying`, `down`, `failed`) to dynamic color HSL tokens.
- Added live stderr tails and last error displays inside detailed folding blocks.
- Wired up a live reconnect button calling `POST /api/mcp/servers/:name/reconnect`.

### C. SQLite-Persisted Micro Support Desk
- **SQLite Database Schema Migration**: Atomic migration registered in [chat-session-store.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/chat-session-store.ts) to define `support_tickets`:
  ```sql
  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS support_tickets (
      ticket_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
      title TEXT NOT NULL,
      description TEXT NOT NULL,
      source TEXT NOT NULL,
      status TEXT NOT NULL,
      severity TEXT NOT NULL,
      created_at TEXT NOT NULL,
      updated_at TEXT NOT NULL,
      resolution_log TEXT,
      metadata_json TEXT
  )
  ```
- **Store Transactions & Persistence**: High-fidelity transactional database routines:
  - `createSupportTicket()`: Generates random secure ticket IDs (`TKT-xxxx`), validates and serializes JSON metadata.
  - `listSupportTickets()`: Restores ticket logs sorted by timestamp, using robust JSON deserialization.
  - `updateSupportTicket()`: Atomic status updating ("Open", "Investigating", "Self-Healing", "Resolved") with concurrent resolution logging for long-term support knowledgebase archival.
  - `deleteSupportTicket()`: Execution of record purge from persistent database store.
- **Unified REST API Router**: Routed full-fidelity controllers in [dashboard-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/dashboard-service.ts):
  - `GET /api/support/tickets`: Returns active tickets log.
  - `POST /api/support/tickets`: Inserts a new support desk ticket, returning status `201 Created`.
  - `POST /api/support/tickets/:ticketId/update`: Atomic update handler.
  - `POST /api/support/tickets/:ticketId/delete`: Purge handler.
- **Frontend Interaction & Persistence**:
  - Wired up tickets queue list hydration inside `#support-tickets-container`.
  - Built an interactive ticket log form allowing user-driven incident reporting with custom metadata capturing (Agent, screen resolution).
  - Integrated manual resolution flow triggering interactive prompts to document bug resolutions in the persistent SQLite database.
  - Integrated the virtual self-healing sweep: transition status to `"self-healing"`, trigger simulated diagnostics log entries in the live trace log, and automatically transition to `"resolved"` with an AI correlation log entry saved to the database.

